President Donald Trump and his administration have prioritized engaging with county commissioners from across the United States. Over 3,700 local officials from all 50 states have participated in the White House State Leadership Conference. Cabinet officials, such as Secretary of the Interior Ryan Zinke and Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue, have emphasized the importance of local input in decision making. State officials and local leaders have praised the administration for its commitment to working closely with them and addressing their concerns. The National Association of Counties has commended the administration for improving intergovernmental partnerships and addressing pressing issues. Overall, the administration's efforts to engage with state and local leaders have been well-received and seen as a positive step towards better collaboration and problem-solving.